["Aq Kupruk is a village in Balkh Province in northern Afghanistan.[1]","Aq Kupruk is also an archaeological site consists of four sites, numbered I, II, III and IV.","Finds included an extensive and sophisticated stone tool industry, very early stone sculpture, domesticated sheep and goat remains, fragments of beaten copper from the ceramic  Neolithic, many projectile points, terracotta and simple jewellery."]